briefdescription.para: Push a message onto the output channel queue.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called by the Scheduler to push a message onto the output channel for downlink.

parameterdescription.para: The index of the channel to push the message to.
Buffer containing the message to push.
Size of the message, in bytes, to push.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is call at application termination and empties the queue, deallocating each message its popped off the queue.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called at when the Reset command is received. It resets all metrics, which include the Sent Counts and the Highwater Marks.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called at when the application is about to load a new configuration table. This will flush the queues and deallocate the messages contained in the queues.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called at when the application has loaded a new configuration table.
if no error occurred. On error, an OSAL error is returned indicating what error occured.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called by the Scheduler to queue a message for downlink.

parameterdescription.para: A CFE_SB_Msg_t pointer that references the software bus message
A #TO_TlmOutputChannelQueue_t pointer to the output channel object.

simplesect.para: if successful. OSAL error if unsuccessful.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called when a ground command is received to query an output channel. This will raise an information event containing text with Sent Count and Highwater Mark.

parameterdescription.para: Index of the output channel to query.

simplesect.para: if successful. FALSE if an error occurred.
